comments: Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Orllwyn Teifi.

Abolished 1894 when the parts in Carmarthenshire and 
    Pembrokeshire became the parishes of East Cilrhedyn 
    and West Cilrhedyn respectively.

Created 1894 from the Carmarthenshire part of the parish of Cilrhedyn. 
    Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Cenarth.
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Orllwyn Teifi.

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of 
    Bettws Evan. See also Table 2, note (c).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Orllwyn Teifi.
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Llandyfriog.

That part which until 1.4.1935 formed part of the parish of 
    Llanfihangel ar Arth. See also Table 2, note (a).

Created 1.4.1897 out of the parish of Cenarth. See also Table 
    2, note (a).
Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of Llanfair Orllwyn, Henllan and Bangor. See also Table 2, note (c).
Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Llangeler

Created 1894 from the Pembrokeshire part of the parish of Cilrhedyn. 
    See also Table 2, note (b).
